canonical:
  title: 留別西京金少尹峻
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 相逢信宿又分離愁見歧中更有歧手裏桂香銷欲盡別君無處話心期
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 留別西京金少尹峻
  author: 崔致遠
  language: lzh
  text: 相逢信宿又分離。愁見歧中更有歧。手裏桂香銷欲盡。別君無處話心期。
korean:
  title: 유별 서경 김소윤 준
  author: 최치원
  language: kor
  text: |-
    서로 만나 수일 만에 또 헤어지게 되니
    갈림길에 또 갈림 있는 것이 시름겹구나
    손 가운데 계향은 다 녹으려 하는데
    그대와 이제 헤어져 마음 얘기 나눌 기약 없구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0060&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: 'Parting at the Western Capital: To Kim So-yun, Administrator Joon'
  author: Choe Chi-won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    We met, yet stayed but a few days before parting ways—
    and sorrow deepens to see fork after fork in the road.
    The cassia fragrance in my palm fades toward nothing,
    and with you gone, no place remains to speak what stirs my heart.
  footnotes:
    - Cassia fragrance (桂香) is a classical allusion to gift-tokens exchanged between parting friends, symbolizing the memory of their bond.
    - The repeated imagery of forking paths suggests both literal journeys and the diverging circumstances of life that separate companions.
